ildren":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/682"},"text":"58 Stat. 682","children":[],"tail":". Title VI of the Act is classified generally to subchapter IV (§ 291 et seq.) of chapter 6A of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s201"},"text":"section 201 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Developmental Disabilities Assistance and Bill of Rights Act of 2000, referred to in subsec. (c)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/402"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–402","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1677"},"text":"114 Stat. 1677","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 144 (§ 15001 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s15001"},"text":"section 15001 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in subsec. (d)(3), (5), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 7 (§ 301 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. Parts A and B of title IV of the Act are classified generally to parts A (§ 601 et seq.) and B (§ 620 et seq.) of subchapter IV of chapter 7 of Title 42. Title XX of the Act is classified generally to subchapter XX (§ 1397 et seq.) of chapter 7 of Title 42. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id80e0f367-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/371/s2/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–371, § 2(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (2) and struck out heading and text of former par. (2). Text read as follows: “Grants under this section for the operation (including initial operating amounts and operating deficits, which include the cost of attracting, training, and retaining qualified personnel) of a demonstration health project, whether or not constructed with amounts authorized by this section, may be made for up to 50 percent of the cost of that operation (or 80 percent of the cost of that operation for a project to be carried out in a county for which a distressed county designation is in effect under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s14526"},"text":"section 14526 of this title","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/371/s2/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–371, § 2(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paragraphs (2) and (3)” for “paragraph (2)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/371/s2/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–371, § 2(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id80e0f368-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id80e0f369-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Advisory Committee","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Advisory committees established after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1973","children":[],"tail":", to terminate not later than the expiration of the 2-year period beginning on the date of their establishment, unless, in the case of a committee established by the President or an officer of the Federal Government, such committee is renewed by appropriate action prior to the expiration of such 2-year period, or in the case of a committee established by the Congress, its duration is otherwise provided by law. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s1013"},"text":"section 1013 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
